            <fr:title text="Flow Matching Definitions"><fr:link href="/lipmanFlowMatchingGenerative2023/" title="Flow Matching for Generative Modeling" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/lipmanFlowMatchingGenerative2023/" display-uri="lipmanFlowMatchingGenerative2023" type="local">Flow Matching</fr:link> Definitions</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>7</fr:month><fr:day>1</fr:day></fr:date><fr:uri>https://kellenkanarios.com/008B/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>008B</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/008B/</fr:route><fr:title text="Probablity density path">Probablity density path</fr:title><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p>The <html:em>probability density path</html:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p: [0,1] \times  \mathbb {R}^d \to  \mathbb {R}_{>0}]]></fr:tex> is a time dependent probability density function i.e. <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\int  p_t(x)\mathrm {d}x = 1]]></fr:tex></html:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>7</fr:month><fr:day>1</fr:day></fr:date><fr:uri>https://kellenkanarios.com/008C/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>008C</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/008C/</fr:route><fr:title text="Time-dependent vector field">Time-dependent vector field</fr:title><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p>We define a <html:em>time-dependent vector field</html:em> as a map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v: [0,1] \times  \mathbb {R}^d \to  \mathbb {R}^d]]></fr:tex></html:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>7</fr:month><fr:day>1</fr:day></fr:date><fr:uri>https://kellenkanarios.com/008D/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>008D</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/008D/</fr:route><fr:title text="Flow">Flow</fr:title><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p>Give a <fr:link href="/008C/" title="Time-dependent vector field" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/008C/" display-uri="008C" type="local">vector field</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v_t]]></fr:tex> one can construct a time-dependent diffeomorphic map called a <html:em>flow</html:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi : [0,1] \times  \mathbb {R}^d \to  \mathbb {R}^d]]></fr:tex> defined via the ordinary differential equation
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\begin {align*}
  \frac {\mathrm {d}}{\mathrm {d}t} \phi _t(x) &= v_t(\phi _t(x)) \\
  \phi _{0}(x) &= x
.\end {align*}]]></fr:tex></html:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
    <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/kellenkanarios/" title="Kellen Kanarios" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/kellenkanarios/" display-uri="kellenkanarios" type="local">Kellen Kanarios</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:taxon>Remark</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
   Modeling a <fr:link href="/008C/" title="Time-dependent vector field" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/008C/" display-uri="008C" type="local">vector field</fr:link> via a neural network i.e. <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v_t(x; \theta )]]></fr:tex> implicitly defines a deep parametric model of the flow <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi _t(x)]]></fr:tex> via solving the ODE or an approximation, such as
   <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\phi _{t + \Delta  t}(x) \approx  \phi _t(x) + \Delta  t \cdot  v_t(\phi _t(x); \theta )]]></fr:tex>
   Obviously, accuracy will be dependent on the step size <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Delta  t]]></fr:tex>.
 </fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
<fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:uri>https://kellenkanarios.com/008E/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>008E</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/008E/</fr:route><fr:title text="Generated probability paths">Generated probability paths</fr:title><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p>We say that a <fr:link href="/008C/" title="Time-dependent vector field" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/008C/" display-uri="008C" type="local">vector field</fr:link> <html:em>generates</html:em> a <fr:link href="/008B/" title="Probablity density path" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/008B/" display-uri="008B" type="local">probability density path</fr:link> if the <fr:link href="/008D/" title="Flow" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/008D/" display-uri="008D" type="local">flow</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v_t]]></fr:tex> satisfies
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[p_t = [\phi _t]_* p_{0},]]></fr:tex>
where
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[[\phi _t]_*p_{0}(x) = p_{0}(\phi _t^{-1}(x)) \det \left [ \frac {\partial  \phi _t^{-1} }{\partial  x}(x) \right ].  ]]></fr:tex></html:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>7</fr:month><fr:day>2</fr:day></fr:date><fr:uri>https://kellenkanarios.com/008I/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>008I</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/008I/</fr:route><fr:title text="Generation via Continuity Equation">Generation via Continuity Equation</fr:title><fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p>
A <fr:link href="/008C/" title="Time-dependent vector field" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/008C/" display-uri="008C" type="local">vector field</fr:link> generates a <fr:link href="/008B/" title="Probablity density path" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/008B/" display-uri="008B" type="local">probability density path</fr:link> if it satisfies the <fr:link href="/EFN0/" title="Continuity Equation" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/EFN0/" display-uri="EFN0" type="local">continuity equation</fr:link>.
</html:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>7</fr:month><fr:day>9</fr:day></fr:date><fr:uri>https://kellenkanarios.com/LRL4/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>LRL4</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/LRL4/</fr:route><fr:title text="Flow Matching Loss"><fr:link href="/lipmanFlowMatchingGenerative2023/" title="Flow Matching for Generative Modeling" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/lipmanFlowMatchingGenerative2023/" display-uri="lipmanFlowMatchingGenerative2023" type="local">Flow Matching</fr:link> Loss</fr:title><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p>Given an initial noise distribution <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex>, a desired data distribution <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q]]></fr:tex>, a <fr:link href="/008B/" title="Probablity density path" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/008B/" display-uri="008B" type="local">probability density path</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p_t]]></fr:tex>, such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p_{0} = p]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p_{1} =q]]></fr:tex>, and a <fr:link href="/008C/" title="Time-dependent vector field" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/008C/" display-uri="008C" type="local">vector field</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u_t]]></fr:tex> that <fr:link href="/008E/" title="Generated probability paths" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/008E/" display-uri="008E" type="local">generates</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p_t]]></fr:tex>. We define the <html:em>flow matching loss</html:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}_{\mathrm {FM}}]]></fr:tex> as
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}_{\mathrm {FM}}(\theta ) \coloneqq  \mathbb {E}_{t, p_t(x)} \|v_t(x; \theta ) - u_t\|]]></fr:tex></html:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
